Twitter Bootstrap 


- Front end - uses client not server
- often for UIs and themes
- uses HTML/CSS/JS
- build responsive mobile first websites - starts mobile -> bigger
- most popular framework as its type - foundation is popular too



Why use frameworks?

- Increased dev speed - style, alignment, position done for you through classes
- responsiveness - grid system makes it mobile friendly
- consistency
- customisable 
- support - has documentation etc  
- frid system and layouts 


HTML Componenets /Helpers
dropdowns, icons, grid, tables, wells, list gorups, forms, buttons, links, labels, jumbotron(showcase), navbar, pagination etc 

JS widgets
Transitions
modals - pop ups
tabs 
sliders
alterts
popovers
tooltips
collapsable elements 


Install methods
- download source files css/js
- cdn
- script tag (not great for offline)
- bower (clientside pacman)
- npm (backend node.js etc)
- jQuery is required for all JS widgets 






Bootstrap cheatsheet (constructing on replitt)

lets go to getbootstrap.com 
https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.1/getting-started/download/
lets grab the basic template and put it in our index


<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <!-- Required meta tags -->
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-1BmE4kWBq78iYhFldvKuhfTAU6auU8tT94WrHftjDbrCEXSU1oBoqyl2QvZ6jIW3" crossorigin="anonymous">

    <title>Hello, world!</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello, world!</h1>

    <!-- Optional JavaScript; choose one of the two! -->

    <!-- Option 1: Bootstrap Bundle with Popper -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-ka7Sk0Gln4gmtz2MlQnikT1wXgYsOg+OMhuP+IlRH9sENBO0LRn5q+8nbTov4+1p" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

    <!-- Option 2: Separate Popper and Bootstrap JS -->
    <!--
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@popperjs/core@2.10.2/dist/umd/popper.min.js" integrity="sha384-7+zCNj/IqJ95wo16oMtfsKbZ9ccEh31eOz1HGyDuCQ6wgnyJNSYdrPa03rtR1zdB" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-QJHtvGhmr9XOIpI6YVutG+2QOK9T+ZnN4kzFN1RtK3zEFEIsxhlmWl5/YESvpZ13" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    -->
  </body>
</html>




- we can see we have doctype
- language
- utf
- character set
- viewport at device width
- title

lets clean up the head and meta tags

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-1BmE4kWBq78iYhFldvKuhfTAU6auU8tT94WrHftjDbrCEXSU1oBoqyl2QvZ6jIW3" crossorigin="anonymous">

    <title>Bootstrap Cheatsheet</title>
  </head>

- we are using minified file here

-after downloading bootstrap locally, the only files we would need are the bootstrap 

